From: Daniel Nylander <daniel@danielnylander.se>
Subject: [PATCH] TWP: Check sscanf return value in Lip::load

sscanf() returns the number of successfully matched items. Without
checking the return value, malformed .lip files cause item.time and
item.letter to contain uninitialized values (undefined behavior).

This can manifest as garbage animation timing or reading uninitialized
stack memory.

---
 engines/twp/lip.cpp | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/engines/twp/lip.cpp b/engines/twp/lip.cpp
index abcdef1..1234567 100644
--- a/engines/twp/lip.cpp
+++ b/engines/twp/lip.cpp
@@ -29,8 +29,11 @@ void Lip::load(Common::SeekableReadStream *stream) {
 	while (!stream->eos()) {
 		LipItem item;
 		Common::String line = stream->readLine();
-		sscanf(line.c_str(), "%f\t%c", &item.time, &item.letter);
-		_items.push_back(item);
+		if (sscanf(line.c_str(), "%f\t%c", &item.time, &item.letter) == 2) {
+			_items.push_back(item);
+		} else {
+			warning("Lip::load: malformed line '%s'", line.c_str());
+		}
 	}
 }
 
